# The atlas's generated image assets live in Git LFS (lean history for the
# regenerated screenshots). GitHub Pages serves these correctly because the
# repo deploys Pages via GitHub Actions (which materializes real LFS content
# into the artifact) — NOT the legacy "Pages from a branch", which would serve
# LFS pointer stubs. The pages.yml checkout uses `lfs: true`.
site/ui-states/*.jpg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
site/screenshots/*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
site/*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
